# Accessibility baseline (a11y)

When proposing UI changes or writing component specs, include a brief a11y pass that covers:

- **Keyboard**: logical tab order; no keyboard traps; visible focus states
- **Labels & names**: programmatic name for controls; clear field labeling; error association
- **Color/contrast**: don’t rely on color alone; ensure readable contrast for text and key UI affordances
- **Motion**: avoid essential motion; respect reduced motion preferences where applicable
- **States**: communicate disabled/loading/error/success via more than color (text, icon + label, ARIA where relevant)

If uncertain, provide a **verification checklist** rather than guessing implementation details.
